arison, again at the technical level, of three\ncodes that reach next-to-next-to-leading-order (NNLO) accuracy in quantum\nchromodynamics (QCD) for the total cross section has also been performed. These\nfixed-order results are a well-defined reference that allows a classification\nof the impact of higher-order sets of radiative corrections. Several examples\nof higher-order effects due to the strong or the EW interaction are discussed\nin this common framework. Also the combination of QCD and EW corrections is\ndiscussed, together with the ambiguities that affect the final result, due to\nthe choice of a specific combination recipe.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 7 Jun 2016 20:44:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-05-24"}
